# .gitattributes — Levithan786/elder-debate-skill
# Chiseled via github-elder-debate skill on 2026-06-12
# Sovereign standards for consistent cross-platform behavior, diff quality, and binary integrity

# This file complements the chiseled .gitignore.
# It enforces normalization and handling rules that protect the spine of sovereign records
# while enabling glorious, frictionless git operations inside any clone.

# =============================================================================
# LINE ENDING NORMALIZATION (Critical for multi-OS tailnet work)
# =============================================================================
# Normalize all text files to LF on commit, convert to native on checkout.
# Prevents CRLF/LF wars across macOS, Linux, and Windows machines in the mesh.
* text=auto

# Explicit text treatment + better diffs for key sovereign file types
*.md           text diff=markdown
*.txt          text
*.py           text diff=python
*.js           text
*.json         text
*.yaml         text
*.yml          text
*.sh           text eol=lf

# Sovereign chiseled records — maximum stability and clarity
SOVEREIGN-CHISELS/** text
SOVEREIGN-CHISELS/*.md text eol=lf diff=markdown

# =============================================================================
# BINARY FILES (Never corrupt with line-ending conversion)
# =============================================================================
*.png          binary
*.jpg          binary
*.jpeg         binary
*.gif          binary
*.ico          binary
*.pdf          binary
*.zip          binary
*.tar.gz       binary
*.rar          binary
*.so           binary
*.dll          binary

# =============================================================================
# FUTURE CODE LIMBS & TOOLING
# =============================================================================
# Prepared for Python (Roh, Cartography, future limbs) and possible Node/web layers
*.py           text eol=lf diff=python
*.ipynb        binary

# =============================================================================
# NOTES & PHILOSOPHY
# =============================================================================
# - text=auto is the balanced sovereign choice: flexible yet consistent.
# - Explicit eol=lf on key files adds extra spine rigidity where it matters most.
# - diff=markdown improves GitHub and git diff readability for chiseled prose.
# - Binary declaration prevents accidental corruption of images and archives.
# - This file itself is tracked and versioned. Local personal overrides can still be
#   created (they are ignored by .gitignore) but the sovereign standard lives here.
# - Future elder debates on git operations shall reference and evolve this file.

